died. We demonstrate the versatility of the numerical scheme in catering for\nirregular and asymmetric initial tumour geometries. We present numerical\nsimulations for both cases and the results are consistent with theoretical and\nheuristic expectations such as early linear growth rate and preservation of\nradial symmetry when the boundary conditions are symmetric.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 7 Jan 2020 10:05:30 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 17 Aug 2020 11:07:46 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 29 Sep 2020 00:01:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-10-21"}
