{"id":"2001.02503","submitter":"William Hager","authors":"William W. Hager and Hongchao Zhang","title":"Convergence rates for an inexact ADMM applied to separable convex\n  optimization","comments":"arXiv admin note: text overlap with arXiv:1604.02494","journal-ref":"Computational Optimization and Application, 77 (2020), 729-754","doi":"10.1007/s10589-020-00221-y","report-no":null,"categories":"math.NA cs.NA","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Convergence rates are established for an inexact accelerated alternating\ndirection method of multipliers (I-ADMM) for general separable convex\noptimization with a linear constraint. Both ergodic and non-ergodic iterates\nare analyzed. Relative to the iteration number k, the convergence rate is\nO(1/k) in a convex setting and O(1/k^2) in a strongly convex setting. When an\nerror bound condition holds, the algorithm is 2-step linearly convergent. The\nI-ADMM is designed so that the accuracy of the inexact iteration preserves the\nglobal convergence rates of the exact iteration, leading to better numerical\nperformance in the test problems.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 6 Jan 2020 22:33:02 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 12 Jan 2020 23:21:23 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 8 Jun 2020 04:02:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-07-20"}
